Description: Provides a unified input-output interface for reading and writing
    bundles — collections of 3-D polylines (streamlines) reconstructed by
    fibre-tracking algorithms applied to diffusion MRI data. Supported formats
    include VTK (.vtk), VTP (.vtp), medInria FDS (.fds), MRtrix TCK/TSF
    (.tck/.tsf), and TrackVis TRK (.trk), with additional formats accessible
    via the 'DIPY' Python library through 'reticulate'. Bundles are represented
    in R using the S7 classes defined in the 'fiber' package: a single tract
    (class 'streamline') stores its coordinates, per-point scalar attributes,
    and per-streamline scalar attributes in separate, typed slots; a collection
    of tracts (class 'bundle') wraps a list of streamlines together with
    optional bundle-level metadata. VTK support is provided at compile time by
    the 'rvtk' package, which supplies pre-compiled VTK libraries and headers
    so that no manual VTK installation is required on most platforms.
